Two separate bus crashes have left 23 people injured at Kwaita village on Abuja-Lokoja road. Twelve people were injured when an unmarked 18-seater bus crashed on Saturday, while 11 others were also injured when a Toyota Previa car with registration number FST 927 XP somersaulted and crashed into a ditch on Friday. A witness  said the bus driver lost control of his steering and  veered off the road, leaving 11 passengers with injuries. He said officials of the Federal Road Safety Commission (FRSC) later arrived the scene to evacuate the injured passengers to hospital. When contacted, the Yangoji unit commander of the FRSC, ACC Samgbaza Joseph, confirmed the accident, which he attributed to speed limit violation. He said those injured were taken to Kwali General Hospital for treatment.